bug.short_desc: Table header scrolls too far if column visibility button is disabled

long_desc.thetext:
As reported by Daniel Hirtzbruch on the ML[1]: When horizontally scrolling all the way to the right in a table that also has a vertical scroll bar and the column visibility button set to disabled, the header cells will scroll to far so they are no longer aligned with the table columns. Daniel also posted a Playground example that shows the problem[2].
[1]http://n2.nabble.com/Table-Bug-td4763857.html;cid=1269017147663-712#a4763857 [2]http://bit.ly/boXDZV
Assigning all table bugs to Martin.

I found what might be a similar case (without disabling column visibility button). In 2.0.2 FCE, if the columns of the left-hand table are made wider so that a horizontal scrollbar is shown, using this scrollbar misplaces columns and their corresponding header cells in IE9.

This bug is still there.
Any plans to fix this?
We don't have a plan to work in it right now.

Created attachment 1287 Screenshot of qooxdoo table with headers misaligned with data
We have various instances of qooxdoo tables that exhibit this failure mode. If the table is configured to disallow the upper-right menu for toggling column selection, and the contents of the table are large enough necessitate both horizontal and vertical scrollbars, then the headers become misaligned with the table contents when the user scrolls to the right side of the table. The misalignment is equal to the width of the vertical scrollbar.
*** Bug 8470 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
